ht next to Victor's (shouting could have been during murder; Nathan claims it was just frustration during the call)\\nLock: door wouldn't shut if it wasn't locked, so Victor locked it sometimes to keep door shut (according to Nathan); Nathan has nothing to say about the missing key because he doesn't live here; Melissa doubts he would've locked it last night because his fireplace keeps the room too warm\\nWindow: Nathan says it was open when they entered the room this morning and Melissa shut it; Victor didn't usually leave it open overnight or sleep with it open\\n\\nMelissa: sick on and off since Nathan was young (degenerative muscular condition treatable but not curable); hardest part is getting insurance to cover things (potential murder motive, getting life insurance money from Victor?); not likely to push over someone Victor's size according to Nathan\\n\\nMelissa & Victor: at each other's throats for years; split up rooms of house & go most days barely speaking; stay married because Victor was religious & has ironclad prenup + Melissa can't afford divorce due to not working & needing his healthcare; Frances suspects Victor was cheating with Ms. Giles (school admin)\\n\\nAccording to Nathan: Frances arrived around 2pm, argued with Victor because he found out she changed her major to something impractical instead of law (her parents' wish), she can't afford school without their help and begged Victor not to say anything. Frances also hasn't told us about her major change even though we're her close friend, so Nathan could be lying to push blame towards her.\\n\\nNathan's secretary sent a recording of the call, and we confirmed he was speaking or yelling for the whole duration (6:55-8:12) without any major breaks. Alibi seems to check out, unless a) he was on his cell phone, lied about not having service, and did the murder during the call, or b) he did the murder between 6:50 (left the sitting room) & 6:55 (call started)\\n\\nFrances: timestamped selfie on her 