 don’t need to completely re-describe theories that have only changed a little, just refer to the earlier theory\\n- You may ignore this box if your theories have not changed at all\",\"I think Melissa is the killer. Frances's alibi was confirmed by her timestamped photo and our retreading of the route from the lake which proved she couldn't have gotten back fast enough. Nathan's alibi was confirmed by the recording of the call with his secretary, showing he didn't have any significant pauses or strange noises during the timeframe of the murder. Melissa's alibi can't be confirmed and her only defense is that she's too frail to have pushed Victor over, but we only have her word for it; she could be stronger than she appears. Nathan also said that her health condition has been \\\"on and off\\\" so maybe she could've had a burst of strength last night. In addition, she seems to have the strongest motive for murdering him because she was trapped in a miserable marriage due to being financially dependent on him, and killing him would be the only way to end the marriage without losing access to his money.\",\"I wasn't very effective at solving the mystery - I never even considered Peanut as a suspect! I was misled by genre convention making me assume that the murder must have been intentional and must have been done by a human, but now after reading the solution, I can see how the clues for Peanut were all there. I think the biggest one I missed is that Frances's lake selfie was her alone, rather than her with Peanut. I did notice that at the time, but chalked it up to her just not including Peanut in the picture rather than Peanut actually not being there.\"][\" \",\"\",\"\",\"I'm investigating the lock because I suspect Frances might be lying about it\",\"\",\"Windows next: could be another point of entry for the murderer\",\"\",\"Body to determine cause of death\",\"\",\"Fireplace for more clues on cause of death\",\"\",\"Vases: why were they smashed?\",\"\",\"Mud: did murderer come from outside?\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"Investigate Nathan's business online to get a sense if he really was on a work call from 6:50-8:10 last night\",\"\",\"Talk to Nathan: currently most suspicious of him\",\"\",\"Ask more about shouting because it seems suspicious\",\"Ask about door locking habits to see if the lock would have been broken pre-murder instead of only this morning\",\"Ask about window to see if it could have been open & responsible for the cold draft Nathan claimed he felt, then shut between then and our arrival to investigate the scene\",\"Missing key: door & lock still very suspicious\",\"Lake timing to check Frances's alibi\",\"Melissa's health: we don't know much about her yet, is her health bad?\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"Call Ferris to check Nathan's alibi since I'm still the most suspicious of him\",\"\",\"Talk to Frances next to confirm Nathan's story about changing her major\",\"First get more detail on her alibi\",\"Second opinion on Melissa's health since we still don't know much about her\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"Check Frances's lake timing to see if she could have lied\",\"\",\"Talk to Melissa next, she's the only one without a seemingly-proven alibi so far\",\"Find out what Melissa was up to during the murder time frame and whether any of it can be proven\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\"]"